---
// Three-step horizontal timeline. Stacks on mobile, separators hide.
---

<section class="section" id="how" data-screen-label="How">
  <div class="container-page">
    <span class="eyebrow">How it works</span>
    <h2
      style="font-size: clamp(28px, 4vw, 40px); letter-spacing: -0.025em; line-height: 1.1; font-weight: 700; color: var(--color-slate-100); margin: 16px 0 0; max-width: 720px; text-wrap: balance;"
    >
      Three steps. One keystroke each.
    </h2>

    <div class="how-grid">
      <div class="how-step">
        <span class="num">1</span>
        <h3>Press the hotkey</h3>
        <p>
          Default <code style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 13px;"
            >Ctrl + PrintScreen</code
          >. Rebind in settings to anything.
        </p>
        <div class="visual">
          <span class="kbd">Ctrl</span>
          <span style="margin: 0 6px; color: var(--color-slate-400);">+</span>
          <span class="kbd">PrtSc</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <span class="arrow-sep">
        <svg
          viewBox="0 0 24 24"
          fill="none"
          stroke="currentColor"
          stroke-width="1.75"
          stroke-linecap="round"
          stroke-linejoin="round"
          width="24"
          height="24"
        >
          <line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"></line>
          <polyline points="12 5 19 12 12 19"></polyline>
        </svg>
      </span>

      <div class="how-step">
        <span class="num">2</span>
        <h3>Drag a region</h3>
        <p>
          The screen dims. Drag any rectangle. Annotate with arrows, boxes, or
          blur a sensitive zone, or skip and ship.
        </p>
        <div
          class="visual"
          style="padding: 0; position: relative; overflow: hidden;"
        >
          <svg
            width="100%"
            height="60"
            viewBox="0 0 280 60"
            preserveAspectRatio="none"
          >
            <rect
              x="40"
              y="10"
              width="200"
              height="40"
              fill="none"
              stroke="#D97757"
              stroke-width="2"
              stroke-dasharray="4 3"></rect>
            <rect
              x="40"
              y="10"
              width="200"
              height="40"
              fill="rgba(217,119,87,0.10)"></rect>
            <circle cx="40" cy="10" r="3" fill="#D97757"></circle>
            <circle cx="240" cy="10" r="3" fill="#D97757"></circle>
            <circle cx="40" cy="50" r="3" fill="#D97757"></circle>
            <circle cx="240" cy="50" r="3" fill="#D97757"></circle>
            <text
              x="240"
              y="35"
              font-size="9"
              font-family="ui-monospace, monospace"
              fill="#D97757"
              text-anchor="end"
              dx="-4">412 × 240</text
            >
          </svg>
        </div>
      </div>

      <span class="arrow-sep">
        <svg
          viewBox="0 0 24 24"
          fill="none"
          stroke="currentColor"
          stroke-width="1.75"
          stroke-linecap="round"
          stroke-linejoin="round"
          width="24"
          height="24"
        >
          <line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"></line>
          <polyline points="12 5 19 12 12 19"></polyline>
        </svg>
      </span>

      <div class="how-step">
        <span class="num">3</span>
        <h3>Paste anywhere</h3>
        <p>
          The link is on your clipboard. Paste into Claude Code, Cursor, Aider.
          Anything that takes an image URL.
        </p>
        <div
          class="visual"
          style="flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start; gap: 4px;"
        >
          <div>
            <span style="color: var(--color-brand);">claude $</span>
            <span style="color: var(--color-slate-100);"> what's broken: </span>
          </div>
          <div style="color: var(--color-indigo-400); font-size: 11px;">
            drive.google.com/uc?id=1aBcD<span
              style="display: inline-block; width: 6px; height: 11px; background: var(--color-slate-100); vertical-align: -1px; margin-left: 2px; animation: blink 1s steps(2) infinite;"
            ></span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
